<p>I want to have matches with 2 teams in my App. Currently I implemented this with a simple hasMany/belongsToMany relationship.</p>  <p>Tables: teams, matches, match_team (match_id, team_id)</p>  <p><strong>Team Model</strong></p>  <pre><code>... public function matches() {   return $this-&gt;belongsToMany('App\Match'); } </code></pre>  <p><strong>Match Model</strong></p>  <pre><code>... public function teams() {   return $this-&gt;belongsToMany('App\Team'); } </code></pre>  <p>So of course I have 2 rows for each match in the Pivot table match_team:</p>  <pre><code>match_id   team_id           1      1000        1      2000        2      3000        2      4000 </code></pre>  <p>With Blade templating engine I can request f.e. the home team like:</p>  <pre><code>{{$match-&gt;teams[0]-&gt;name}} </code></pre>  <h3>But I want to be more specific and want to have a table like this:</h3>  <pre><code>match_id   host_team   guest_team        1        1000         2000        2        3000         4000 </code></pre>  <p>But then I don't really know how to set those relationships...</p>  <p>Any thoughts/ideas on that? =)</p>